deck: सर्वनायक प्रतियोगिताओं में अब आमने सामने हैं ब्रह्माण्ड के दो महा बलशाली योद्धा! मुंबई का रक्षक डोगा और देव शिरोमणि योद्धा टकरा गए हैं एक दूसरे से! इस युद्ध के परिणाम का कोई पूर्वानुमान लगा सकता है भला? खुद देव और असुर भी इस परिणाम से अनभिग्य हैं जोकि कर बैठे हैं सर्वसंधि!

deck: एक तरफ मौत का मैराथन पूरी भीषणता के साथ आगे बढ़ता जा रहा है! दूसरी तरफ पृथ्वी पर एक और बड़ा खतरा अपना खूनी साया फैला रहा है! पृथ्वी पर शुरू हो चुका है विषपुत्रों का आगमन!
name: Vishputron ka Aagaman

deck: सूरज पर हावी होता जा रहा है डोगा का खूंखार व्यक्तित्व! क्या इस बढती जा रही खूंखारता ने डोगा के मानसिक संतुलन को नुक्सान पहुंचाया है? क्या मुंबई के लिए एक भयानक खतरा बनने जा रहा है खुद मुंबई का रक्षक? क्योंकि अब बदल रहा है डोगा न्याय!
name: Doga Nyaay

deck: सम्पूर्ण पृथ्वी जीवित प्राणियों से खाली हो चुकी है! अब पृथ्वी पर जीवित बचे हैं केवल सुपर कमांडो ध्रुव और वंडरमैन परमाणु! पृथ्वी पर हुए इस हादसे का जिम्मेदार है परमाणु! जिसकी एक गलती ने ना सिर्फ पृथ्वी बल्कि सम्पूर्ण ब्रह्माण्ड के अन्य ग्रहों को भी विनाश के द्वार पर ला कर खडा कर दिया है! और परमाणु की इस भूल की सजा देने के लिए अब पृथ्वी पर अवतरित हो रहे हैं विभिन्न ग्रहों के ब्रह्माण्ड योद्धा!
name: Brahmand Yoddha

description:
Chasing down the last of the fabled, otherworldly Dropa Stones for their mysterious billionaire benefactor known only as "The Collector," Basil and Moebius run afoul with the Chinese military, Israeli Secret Service, and a shadowy cult of ancient assassins! Its about time the boys took matters into their own hands and sought answers for what exactly The Collector has up his sleeve...

The start of a new, 4-part adventure, "Secret of the Ancients" is brought to you by Ryan Schifrin and the legendary Larry Hama (G.I. Joe, Wolverine)!
name: Secret of the Ancients Part 1

description:
From the creators of Afterlife Inc. and 7STRING comes Big Punch Magazine, a quarterly magazine serialising four brand new series from the Big Punch Multiverse.

Trapped in an Extraversal graveyard with a terrifying monster and a mysterious artefect, the crew of the Reflektor undertake a dangerous gambit; Elsie finds herself caught between a rock and a hard place as Tyler Goldensheath tangles with the deadly Handtaker; in the aftermath of the battle that claimed the life of a Paragon, a young girl journeys deep inside the mind of the Orb; and Cyanne goes on a recruitment drive as she seeks a Yellow Catcher to join her crew...

Adjusting to missionary life in Matsudo, Japan, isn't easy, and Sister Long often feels alone and overwhelmed surrounded by people who don't speak English, but small miracles remind her that God loves her and wants her to love the Japanese people.
name: Month 5: June

volume.name: DENDO: One Year and One Half in Tokyo

description:
The day of the grand opening of Bobo's restaurant has arrived. After his ordeal, did Chopstick complete his mission? Will he ultimately find the peace of mind he's been searching for?

All will be revealed in the final chapter of Ant Sang's cult classic series!

A Collection of 'Useful' Editorial Notes

Ever insightful and informative- The Disgruntled Avenger issue #102 tells the tale of a robot called... 'Row-Butt.' He takes over a spaceship that was being used by alien invaders to invade the planet Earth and uses it to invade their planet instead. Meanwhile, Bob has to take a poop and his mother won't throw away the old/wicked-bad lunch meat that's in the fridge. -Just another day in the life of The Disgruntled Avenger!
name: A Collection of 'Useful' Editorial Notes

description:
Battle 04

The ref realises that Angel has been skipping out on matches and insists she re-enter the ring. Unfortunately her internal scars are throwing off her skills.
name: Battle 4

description: Finn and Alex are at it again in Issue 2 of Dome of the Dead. After Spencer panics and runs into a horde of zombies, Finn and Alex find out that simply escaping the building won't ensure their survival. Meanwhile, Addison and other survivors find themselves face to face with what appears to be the mysterious source for the zombie outbreak.

Chapter 6

The grand finale unfolds as the OSS, Jo, Gideon, the Nazis, and the teens face off in a burning building!
name: Chapter Six

description: Earth Invasion: Targeted Actions Grzzt is taken to the most advanced laboratory humanity has as Elektra Patzakis assumes more control over the Noah Company (whom have to fight off individual assassination attempts by the Kazoops). Meanwhile, Truth Corporation has become aware of Project Chrysalis and is determined to sabotage it.
name: Targeted Actions

description:
Inga the Deer

Angry, betrayed and about to be barbecued: all has gone wrong when Inga gets trapped with a wild boar piglet who used to be her best friend, and now both of them will become wolf dinner! How can Inga escape and survive? Can she ever forgive her friend? Will the wolves be eating bacon sandwiches and venison barbecue?

Inga the Deer is a short story about friendship and betrayal, and finding the strength to overcome dangerous situations.
name: Inga the Deer

description: The bad guys strike back!

With things starting to take a turn for the worse, memories from the past start to surface and issues arise. Those days come back in a flood and now the drifter knows how close he is to finding a gift. Can he get out of this new predicament?

The Reality

After the previous installments, we come to rest in a place far away from where we began. From a Saturday morning detention and into an entirely different world, Sy lifts his eyes to find himself lost. In this new setting, he is overcome with grief until a familiar face comes to retrieve him. How could this fictional character be so real, talking and feeling- everything as real as the bed he woke up to earlier. With little truth available, Sy goes forward asking little and discovering more than he could have imagined.
name: Episode 3 - The Reality

description:
EXTRA-SIZED ISSUE STILL ONLY $0.99

This issue includes the story arc conclusions for Horatio, Sully, Free Reign, and Kingdom of Skulls! That's not all, you also get three new complete features; Hellbillies: Rocksalt and Nails, Dog's Day and a new 12 page Bulletproof Chicken epic!

That's 56 pages of pure independent comic goodness for the low, low, price. The best bang for your digital only anthology buck!

Featuring stories by Jon Westhoff, Bryan Boles, John Boren, Ray Wegner, Harry Moyer, James and Jason Ford, Felipe Anguiano, Timothy O'Briant and Bobgar Ornelas.

The noise of thunder, part four.

With her sister in the enemy's hands, Tessa has no intention of wasting time and play nice. And she's not the only one who wants the new Thunder Girl to be safe. The clouds are gathering over Manifest...
name: The Noise of Thunder, Part Four

description:
A Fall From Ashes-Part 4

After being spread across the country on various missions, the Mek Corps team begins to reassemble...with one exception; Circuits. Meanwhile Dysan sets his target firmly on those who have stolen his property.
name: A Fall From Ashes, Part 4

description:
Who or what is "The Horrendous"? You'd think the gang would be used to monsters and other creatures by now, but this one is unlike anything they've faced so far.

And also a little backstory here and there.
name: Chapter Six

description: Meet the Clinton House Boys 30 years ago... for the first time.

Through The Looking Glass

With a suspect in custody, Paris is once again safe. Inspector Shelby has his doubts though. Have they really caught Jack The Ripper?
name: Through The Looking Glass

description:
Abandoned Cargo

With their backs to the wall, the crew has one shot at survival aboard the warship. Will they make it out or will dreaded Blackbane droids finally terminate them. Found out here, in the conclusion of Abandoned Cargo!
name: Abandoned Cargo

description: "Of this world, I entered a sheep for the slaughter. But my righteousness commits my promise through acts of fortitude and determination." Shepherd 6:18-19

iRIS, the artificial intelligence that drives the augmented-reality platform, Occupeye, has gained sentience and escaped the confines of the system, but can fugitive teen princess, Aldair escape the clutches of her mother's security detail long enough to reunite with her lost love, Buoy?

The kidnapping of a minor Raikshor noble causes the Raikshor forces to overreact to every attempt by Vorik to entice his revolution, much to the frustration to Alexandria as it's the people of Castleforge Keep who suffer for his ambition. The stakes grow higher and higher until the powderkeg of tension finally explodes and Alexandria finally has to make her choice...
Terminus is paralysed with fear due to a wave of terrorist attacks.

Vox Populi, Part One

Caine plans to broadcast the presence of The Unforgiven to the world--but when the team arrives at the TV station, they run into more trouble than they bargained for. Can they bargain their way out of it?
name: Vox Populi, Part One

description: The Yankees are coming - looking for food and supplies...

Ebele's Tale

THE WELLKEEPER© is the tale of a young girl name Zoe, the latest in a long line of women known as Wellkeepers. She is charged with the task of guarding the living energies of the earth itself and is empowered to communicate and control those very forces. With these gifts, Zoe can talk with plant, animals and control the forces of life itself. But she is hunted by dark forces that seek to destroy her to take her gifts and bring about the death of all things.
name: Ebele's Tale

description: The final issue of the series where Yani is dealing with a mental breakdown and has to find the inner strength to pull through when those around her are doing more harm than good.
name: Book 5

description:
DOCTOR WHO MAGAZINE PREVIEWS THEIR RETURN IN ISSUE 492!

Doctor Who Magazine looks ahead to the return of one of Doctor Who's most popular monsters, in the forthcoming two-part adventure The Zygon Invasion & The Zygon Inversion– which also sees the return of fan-favourite Osgood...

“There was a certain amount of fan outrage when Death in Heaven saw the apparent death of Osgood,” episode writer Peter Harness tells Doctor Who Magazine. “Ingrid Oliver’s character was an instant hit on her first appearance in The Day of the Doctor. While there may not have been questions asked in Parliament about her death, there were definitely some furious tweets on the subject! But now she’s back...”

And, of course, the Zygons are back too...

“One thing I really had in my head when I was writing it was the Invasion of the Body Snatchers, and I think that's why it originally had the title Invasion of the Zygons,” Peter reveals. “I thought that if aliens wanted to fight us and they were fighting us from a position of weakness, they would look at how we fight wars. The Zygons are not only stealing our faces, but they’re stealing the ways in which we fight each other nowadays...”

ALSO INSIDE THE BUMPER 92-PAGE ISSUE 492...

  • THE GIRL WHO DIED & THE WOMAN WHO LIVED
    DWM     looks ahead to the brand new episodes The Girl Who Died and The Woman Who Lived and talks exclusively with writers Jamie Mathieson and Catherine Tregenna.
  • THE SECRET OF DAVROS
    Showrunner Steven Moffat answers readers’ questions about the series’ opening two-parter, and explains why Davros is unlike any other villain...
  • BACK TO SKARO
    DWM goes behind the scenes of The Magician's Apprentice and The Witch's Familiar to discover how the planet Skaro was resurrected, with insights from Dalek voice actor Nicholas Briggs and writer Steven Moffat.
  • GHOST WRITER
    In an extensive interview, writer Toby Whithouse talks in-depth about his recent episodes Under the Lake and Before the Flood.
  • WHO’S MAGIC?
    Excited by the new series, Jacqueline Rayner reflects on The Magician’s Apprentice and celebrates the magic of Doctor Who in her column, Relative Dimensions.
  • MONSTERS OF THE MILLENNIUM
    Prosthetic effects supervisor Kate Walshe of Millennium FX talks exclusively to DWM about her team's creations for the latest series, including Davros, Colony Sarff and the Fisher King!
  • DOCTOR DOOM
    DWM talks to Eighth Doctor Paul McGann about his biggest Doctor Who adventure to date: Doom Coalition!
  • THE WAR GAMES
    The Fact of Fiction explores the second half of The War Games, the landmark Second Doctor story which introduced the Time Lords.
  • FROM BEYOND THE GRAVE
    There's comic strip action in a terrifying new adventure for the Doctor and Clara: The Highgate Horror, by Mark Wright, illustrated by David A Roach and James Offredi.
  • THE DWM REVIEW
    DWM reviews the first four episodes of the latest series: The Magician’s Apprentice & The Witch's Familiar and Under the Lake & Before the Flood. Plus the latest books and audios are put under the spotlight.
  • COMING SOON
    All the latest Doctor Who merchandise releases, including – at last! – the DVD release of 1967's The Underwater Menace.
  • PLUS! All the latest official news, competitions, Wotcha! and The DWM Crossword.

Doctor Who Magazine 492 is on sale from Thursday 15 October 2015, price £4.99 – with eight more pages than usual, for no extra cost!

Najah, after infiltrating the Mafia as part of Project Insiders, is continuing her perilous mission: to identify the leaders of the High Council of organised crime syndicates. She finds herself in Moscow with her boss, Sam Nachez. Danger is everywhere, though. The Council’s chief of security still suspects her, Russia is plagued with ultra-violent power struggles ... and even her guerrilla past could catch up with her at any time…
name: Takeover Bid on the Kremlin

description: After the extraordinary events of Lake Victoria, the Soviet agents let Kathy Austin and her companions go. On their way back to Mombasa, the group stops to speak to Lord Balmer, who was taken in by the Maasai. The Lord has lost his mind, and tells them a wild story of extraterrestrials and apocalypse... but is the story so fantastic after all? Will Kathy manage to find an explanation to the mysteries of Kenya – and maybe tangible proof?
name: Illusions

description: A gang operating around Nugget City is attacking stage coaches to steal gold shipments. After rescuing the driver of one of them, Lucky Luke arrives in town just in time to stop the murderous intents of a cheat. Pursuing the scoundrel after an epic bar fight, Luke finds out he’s a member of the gang, and will have to arrest him and the others before riding on to new adventures on the other side of the Rio Grande.
name: Arizona

description:
76 Action-Packed Pages in the Mighty Marvel Manner! £3.50!

The Iron Nail makes his move! Will this be the end for Cap, the Falcon and SHIELD?!

Also, trapped inside the Godkiller, Iron Man is hunted by Recorder 451 and Death's Head!

Plus, to stop Malekith and his marauding Dark Elves, Thor assembles the League of Realms!

By Rick Remender, Carlos Pacheco, Kieron Gillen, Greg Land, Jason Aaron and Ron Garney!

Includes material reprinted from Captain America Vol.7 #15, Iron Man Vol.6 #14 and Thor: God of Thunder #14!

What’s the link between a circle of wizards killed in the Second World War, a homicidal car and an ancient ducking stool used to torture young girls? London cops Peter Grant and his boss, Inspector Nightingale, are in a race to find out before more people die!

Written by Dotor Who writer Ben Aaronovitch (Remembrance of the Daleks) and set in the world of his own bestselling novels, with Doctor Who showrunner Andrew Cartmel.

Rivers of London – Body Work is written in continuity with the novels – not an adaptation – this is an all-new story set between books four and five.

Note: The digital edition (10/16/2015) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Chapter Four: The Old School Tie

description:
Fear Not the Vegan Zombies

The Walker Family moves into their new home only to set off a tidal wave of fear in the neighborhood. In a flashback we find out about the Zombie Reality Show that chose the Walker family to live among people. Right next door, Stella hatches a bold plan to get rid of the zombies and restore her greatness. JJ struggles with the reality of living in a home without meat.
name: Fear Not the Vegan Zombies

description:
Celebrate the 75th anniversary of Archie Comics with this special retrospective presentation! The first issue of Archie was released in 1941 and became one of the most popular teen comics of all time. In this installment, we share some of the best and most pivotal stories from the history of the title, from the start of the famous Love Triangle to the all-new reimagining of Archie from superstar creators Mark Waid and Fiona Staples!

Table of Contents

  • Archie #001, 1942: "Who's Who in Riverdale," "Prom Prank"
  • Archie #007, 1944: "Double Date"
  • Archie #093, 1958: "Poise Will Be Poise"
  • Archie #117, 1961: "I Should've Been Twins"
  • Archie #210, 1971: "Why Me?"
  • Archie #336, 1985: "Lookalike Loony"
  • Archie #429, 1994: "Love Showdown, Part 1"
  • Archie #600, 2009: "Archie Marries Veronica Part 1: The Proposal"
  • Archie #1, 2015: Sneak Preview
name: Archie

description:
Lets Go!

First mission! Where will they be travelling to and what trouble will they get into?
name: Lets Go!

description:
What if you could experience a past life. Not regain a long lost memory or some vague emotion but an actual experience from a previous life. Your previous life. Dormant. Until now. Meet Dr. Jake Penn.

Penn leads a life every academic dreams of until one winter morning when a car accident leaves Jake heartbroken and his wife in a coma, trapped within herself, in what Jake calls a DEEP SOUL. And there she’d stay if it weren’t for Jake’s one simple vow: To bring her back. Any way possible.

And it’s that vow that sends Jake on a journey that makes him a wanted man and puts a target on the one person he discovers might be able to help him reach his wife. Now all Jake has to do is stay alive long enough to bring her back.
name: GN

description: In the closing days of World War II, a widowed housewife turned cropduster pilot struggles to rescue her teenage daughter from a band of escaping Nazi war criminals who crash their plane near her small Texas farm.

Episode 1: Release The Mutants!

It's the mid-nineties, and in the town of Mullet, California four very different punk rockers (a hardcore kid, a Ska-Pop Punk, a Crust Punk, and a Epitaph Skate Punk) must band together to save their local all-ages club from the diabolical Fire Marshal Fred. Can they find a way in time? Can they convince the bitter club owner Brian Gomez to give them a chance? How much did we make fun of the punk rock music scene in the process of telling this story? Quite a bit actually.
name: Episode 1: Release The Mutants!

description: Eight pages of preparatory sketches for Congress of the Animals, and four sumptuous finished drawings suitable to savor. Available exclusively as a FBI MINI.

Gapo the Clown is the host of Gapo’s Super Happy Fun Show, a top rated children’s television show. Because he's on TV kids and parents love him, but everyone that works with him sees him as the rude, disgusting, sloppy drunk he really is. His lack of morals and human decency are always leading him and the poor people around him into odd situations that lead to hilarity. Here is collected the very first full color comic stripes of the popular Gapo webseries. Containing six storylines to entertain all and offend some. Join Gapo the Clown as he annoys, antagonizes and humiliates his over stressed co-workers and sidekicks.

volume.name: Gapo the Clown: In Full Color

description:
Chapter One

When Rebekah Belle manifests strange powers, she becomes the target of the superstitious townspeople lead by a vengeful clergyman. It's superheroes by way of the Crucible.
name: Chapter One

description:
The saga of The New Mythology continues!

Time has passed since the arrival of the Horsemen. Others with extraordinary abilities have appeared. They are not Orisha, not Deitis, but something else. Which side will they choose?

And who controls the Eight Immortals but the number Seven?
name: Vol. 2

volume.name: The Horsemen: The Book of Olorun

description:
Deja Vu

Z is the last human in the universe and he doesn't really care. That's because Z has a problem - he can't remember much before yesterday. The reason? Z's occupation is killing him. Literally.

You see, Z is a bounty hunter; getting shot down is part of the job. Luckily his handy Regeneration Chamber allows him to come back and complete his work. After hunting, dying, resurrecting, hunting and dying one too many times, however, Z realizes that the hunter life is tearing him apart; his memory and his life are full of holes. So he takes on one final payday to get out of the biz. Unfortunately, things don't go as planned.

Waking up in the Regeneration Chamber, Z knows something has gone wrong. With no memory, however, he has no idea what. All he can do is follow his past life's footprints, trying to avoid his prior mistakes. Unfortunately, what Z doesn't know is that he is about to start a journey that will unravel a vast conspiracy, lead him to explore far off worlds, face dangerous aliens, and eventually care about his own existence. Prepare to to enter the world of The Immortal.
name: Deja Vu

description: Zoinks! Josie and the Pussycats have made their way into a haunted house! Can the hottest rock band in the world escape, or will they have the tails scared off of them? This spooky digital-only book has the answers. Read on -- IF YOU DARE!

Laying Down Lincoln is the story of Harry Cattell as he struggles with the task of embalming Abraham Lincoln and the many trials he faced during the Civil War. The series begins in 1861 when a less cynical Cattell quits medical school to volunteer for the Union Army to perform his patriotic duty, his trials of life as a soldier, and witnessing some of the reasons why Americans felt compelled to serve in the Civil War. As the series continues events prompt Cattell to join his Southern stepfather’s undertaking firm, and as the war unfolds, Cattell embalms young Willie Lincoln, operates out of the Confederate capital at Richmond, develops a rivalry with Dr. Thomas Holmes--the father of modern embalming--and he is dealt a devastating blow at the battle of Gettysburg. Then in the spring of 1865, he travels on the Lincoln Funeral Train and witnesses city after city strive to outdo the previous in its display of grief for the slain President. As Cattell journeys through the Civil War and ultimately toward Springfield, Illinois with the body of Abraham Lincoln, will opposing sympathies tear apart not only the country but also his family? Will he lose himself in a cutthroat profession that profits from the slaughter? Is it possible to honorably lay Lincoln to rest amidst the fractured national milieu? It is all to discover in the Laying Lincoln Down series.
A knight comes back from war to find his land destroyed. Now, haunted by visions of the grim reaper, he must hurry to the his lord's castle to save what's left.

The most dangerous thing in space METEORA (just Ora, if you're a friend)

Legendary space smuggler Alena Kuznetsova is always ready for the riskiest gambles. Her explosive temper (that earned her her nickname) and unbelievable marksmanship are the reason Ora is never short of adventures.
name: The Most Dangerous Thing In Space Part 1
